frameDefinitions: A Group is described as having members which are similar or dissimilar to each other.
There is a certain physical Distance within which some other entity can participate in an Event (typically perception or manipulation) with the Participant.
An Entity is at a particular stage of its development.
Some Content is part of the mental model of a Cognizer.
This frame has to do with nouns denoting types of entities.
Two or more distinct entities, which may be concrete or abstract objects or types, are characterized as being similar to each other.
frameExamples: The <t>diversity</t> of students here is to be applauded . INI
I'm sorry, but he was well within the blast <t><fex name='dis'>range</fex></t>.
The <t>Next Generation</t> Internet (NGI) Program has been successfully completed.
I don't like this newfangled <t><fex name='Subtype'>kind</fex></t> of  fish.

A mulberry is very <t>similar</t> in shape
to a loganberry
listRoleDefinitions: This role marks constituents that express the set of objects or types whose diversity is at issue.
This role marks constituents which express a property in respect to which the similarity of the <fen>Group</fen> is assessed.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the Group is diverse or homogenous.
The <fen>Place</fen> is the general area in which diversity occurs or exists.
A type of occurrence whose effects extend a certain distance.
An entity that is conceived as driving the <fen>Event</fen>.
An entity which is deployable by the <fen>Participant</fen> to interact with things within a certain distance.
The spatial extent over which the <fen>Participant</fen> can interact in an <fen>Event</fen>.
The object that has reached a particular stage of its development.
The time at which the progress occurs.
The fact or idea which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> is aware of.
The category whose applicability to the <fen>Content</fen> is known.
The time when the <fen>Cognizer</fen> has awareness (or lack thereof) of the <fen>Content</fen>.
The entity which denotes a subtype of the more general <fen>Category</fen>.
The more general type that the target denotes a subtype of. This role is obligatory and should be labeled DNI when not present.
This role marks constituents that express the set of objects or types whose similarity is at issue.

When there is an asymmetry, <fen>Entity_1</fen> is the entity characterized by its similarity to <fen>Entity_2</fen>, whose characteristics are assumed to be known.  <fen>Entity_1</fen> is often an external argument.

When the <fen>Entities</fen> are expressed separately, <fen>Entity_2</fen> is the one whose characteristics are assumed to be known; it serves as a basis for establishing characteristics of <fen>Entity_1</fen>.
This role marks constituents which express a property in respect to which the similarity of the entities is assessed.
A fact about <fen>Entity_1</fen> or the <fen>Entities</fen> that reveals how <fen>Entity_1</fen> is the same or different from other entities.  (Note the contrast with 'as to'.)
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the similarity occurs or exists.
The Place is the general area in which similarity occurs or exists
